<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id12279fdb-e3ef-11ef-8e9f-f6e47fd25777" identifier="/us/usc/t44/s1326"><num value="1326">§ 1326.</num><heading> Librarian of Congress: reports</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Five thousand copies of the annual and special reports of the Librarian of Congress submitted to Congress, shall be printed and bound in cloth for the Library of Congress.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id12279fdc-e3ef-11ef-8e9f-f6e47fd25777">(<ref href="/us/pl/90/620">Pub. L. 90–620</ref>, <date date="1968-10-22">Oct. 22, 1968</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/82/1270">82 Stat. 1270</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id12279fdd-e3ef-11ef-8e9f-f6e47fd25777">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="historicalAndRevision" id="id12279fde-e3ef-11ef-8e9f-f6e47fd25777"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Historical and Revision Notes</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Based on 44 U.S. Code, 1964 ed., § 156 (<date date="1904-02-24">Feb. 24, 1904</date>, No. 8, <ref href="/us/stat/33/583">33 Stat. 583</ref>).</p>
</note>
